commands.description: The route for the abis folder

productions.doc_descr: a human-readable representation of a Solidity smart contract

members.name: address
members.description: the address for the ABI

members.name: name
members.description: the filename of the ABI (likely the smart contract address)

members.name: path
members.description: the folder holding the abi file

members.name: fileSize
members.description: the size of this file on disc

members.name: lastModDate
members.description: the last update date of the file

members.name: isKnown
members.description: true if this is the ABI for a known smart contract or protocol

members.name: isEmpty
members.description: true if the ABI could not be found (and won't be looked for again)

members.name: nFunctions
members.description: if verbose, the number of functions in the ABI

members.name: nEvents
members.description: if verbose, the number of events in the ABI

members.name: hasConstructor
members.description: if verbose and the abi has a constructor, then `true`, else `false`

members.name: hasFallback
members.description: if verbose and the abi has a fallback, then `true`, else `false`

members.name: functions
members.description: the functions for this address

productions.doc_descr: a human-readable representation of a Solidity function call or event
productions.contained_by: abi, log, receipt, result, slurp, trace, transaction

members.name: name
members.description: the name of the interface

members.name: type
members.description: the type of the interface, either 'event' or 'function'

members.name: signature
members.description: the canonical signature of the interface

members.name: encoding
members.description: the signature encoded with keccak

members.name: inputs
members.description: the input parameters to the function, if any

members.name: outputs
members.description: the output parameters to the function, if any

productions.doc_descr: an input or output parameter to a Solidity function or event

members.name: type
members.description: the type of this parameter

members.name: name
members.description: the name of this parameter

members.name: strDefault
members.description: the default value of this parameter, if any

members.name: indexed
members.description: `true` if this parameter is indexed

members.name: internalType
members.description: for composite types, the internal type of the parameter

members.name: components
members.description: for composite types, the parameters making up the composite

commands.description: The route for the chunks folder

productions.doc_descr: internal-use only data model detailing a single index chunk file

members.name: range
members.description: the block range (inclusive) covered by this chunk

members.name: magic
members.description: an internal use only magic number to indicate file format

members.name: hash
members.description: the hash of the specification under which this chunk was generated

members.name: nAddresses
members.description: the number of addresses in this chunk

members.name: nAppearances
members.description: the number of appearances in this chunk

members.name: size
members.description: the size of the chunk in bytes

members.name: rangeDates
members.description: if verbose, the block and timestamp bounds of the chunk (may be null)

productions.doc_descr: shows first and last timestamps and dates for a given block range

commands.description: The route for the monitors folder

productions.doc_descr: a local file indicating a user's interest in an address. Includes caches for reconicilations, transactions, and appearances as well as an optional association to named account

members.name: address
members.description: the address of this monitor

members.name: name
members.description: the name of this monitor (if any)

members.name: nRecords
members.description: the number of appearances for this monitor

members.name: fileSize
members.description: the size of this monitor on disc

members.name: lastScanned
members.description: the last scanned block number

members.name: isEmpty
members.description: `true` if the monitor has no appearances, `false` otherwise

members.name: isStaged
members.description: `true` if the monitor file in on the stage, `false` otherwise

members.name: deleted
members.description: `true` if this monitor has been deleted, `false` otherwise

commands.description: The route for the names folder

productions.doc_descr: an association between a human-readable name and an address used throughout TrueBlocks

members.name: tags
members.description: colon separated list of tags

members.name: address
members.description: the address associated with this name

members.name: name
members.description: the name associated with this address (retrieved from on-chain data if available)

members.name: symbol
members.description: the symbol for this address (retrieved from on-chain data if available)

members.name: source
members.description: user supplied source of where this name was found (or on-chain if name is on-chain)

members.name: decimals
members.description: number of decimals retrieved from an ERC20 smart contract, defaults to 18

members.name: deleted
members.description: `true` if deleted, `false` otherwise

members.name: isCustom
members.description: `true` if the address is a custom address, `false` otherwise

members.name: isPrefund
members.description: `true` if the address was one of the prefund addresses, `false` otherwise

members.name: isContract
members.description: `true` if the address is a smart contract, `false` otherwise

members.name: isErc20
members.description: `true` if the address is an ERC20, `false` otherwise

members.name: isErc721
members.description: `true` if the address is an ERC720, `false` otherwise
